questions.question_text: Write a program to check if a number is an Armstrong number or not.
questions.description: An Armstrong number is a number that is equal to the sum of its own digits each raised to the power of the number of digits. For example, 153 is an Armstrong number because 1^3 + 5^3 + 3^3 = 153.

questions.question_text: Write a program to check if a string is a palindrome or not.
questions.description: A palindrome is a word, phrase, number, or other sequence of characters that reads the same forward and backward.

questions.question_text: Write a program to generate the first n Fibonacci numbers.
questions.description: The Fibonacci sequence is a series of numbers in which each number is the sum of the two preceding ones, usually starting with 0 and 1.
